how much does an average elephant weigh

The weight of an average elephant can vary depending on the species. The African elephant, which is the largest land mammal, can weigh between 5,000 to 14,000 pounds (2,268 to 6,350 kilograms). The smaller Asian elephants typically weigh between 4,000 to 11,000 pounds (1,814 to 4,990 kilograms). These are average weights, and there can be variations depending on age, sex, and individual differences within each species.
